      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/175/5860",
      "text": [
        " : \"مَنْ مَلَكَ نَفْسَهُ إِذَا رَغِبَ وَ إِذَا رَهِبَ وَ إِذَا اِشْتَهَى وَ إِذَا غَضِبَ وَ إِذَا رَضِيَ حَرَّمَ اَللَّهُ جَسَدَهُ عَلَى اَلنَّارِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5860 - Ibn Faddal narrated from Ghalib ibn Uthman, from Shuayb Al-Aqarqufi, from Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as), peace be upon him, who said:\n\"Whoever controls himself in moments of desire, fear, craving, anger, and satisfaction, Allah (swt) will make his body forbidden to the Fire.\""
        ]
      }
